Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and roughly chop @scallions{2}. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (quarter both limes for 4). Drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%ounce}.

Pat @chicken legs{16%ounce} dry with paper towels. Drizzle with @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}; season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Place skin sides up on prepared #baking sheet{}. Roast until browned and cooked through, ~{28-32%minutes}.

> TIP: If chicken skin isn't crispy yet, broil for 2-3 minutes.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallions, 2 TBSP olive oil (3 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch of garlic to taste, and juice from 1 lime wedge (2 wedges for 4). Season generously with salt and pepper. Taste and add more garlic or lime juice if you feel like something is missing.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic. Cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), remaining Southwest spice, salt, and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}. In a second #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, half the lime zest, juice from 1 lime wedge (2 wedges for 4), and salt. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining lime zest, and juice from any remaining lime wedges to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice and chicken between plates. Top rice with bean mixture and lime crema. Drizzle chicken with chimichurri.